Version 1.1.0 of the Proxmox 9 Installation Setup on Debian 13 Trixie
Summary:
This major version upgrade migrates the installation from Debian 12 (Bookworm) to Debian 13 (Trixie) and from Proxmox VE 8 to Proxmox VE 9. All dependencies, repositories, and kernel versions have been updated to ensure compatibility with the latest Debian and Proxmox releases.

Changes:

1. Debian Version Upgrade:
   - Upgraded base system from Debian 12 (Bookworm) to Debian 13 (Trixie)
   - Updated all references and documentation to reflect Debian 13
   - Directory name changed from /Proxmox-Debian12 to /proxmox-debian13

2. Proxmox Version Upgrade:
   - Upgraded Proxmox VE from version 8 to version 9
   - Updated repository from "bookworm" to "trixie" (trixie pve-no-subscription)
   - Updated GPG key from proxmox-release-bookworm.gpg to proxmox-release-trixie.gpg

3. Kernel Updates:
   - Updated kernel removal pattern from linux-image-6.1* to linux-image-6.12*
   - Compatible with Proxmox VE 9 default kernel (proxmox-default-kernel)

4. Repository Changes:
   - Repository URL: http://download.proxmox.com/debian/pve trixie pve-no-subscription
   - GPG Key URL: https://enterprise.proxmox.com/debian/proxmox-release-trixie.gpg

5. Script Updates:
   - All scripts updated to version 1.1.0
   - All path references updated from /Proxmox-Debian12 to /proxmox-debian13
   - All user-facing messages updated to reference Debian 13 and Proxmox 9
   - Directory paths use lowercase for consistency (proxmox-debian13)

6. Dependency Compatibility:
   - Verified all packages (proxmox-ve, postfix, open-iscsi, chrony) compatibility with Debian 13
   - Maintained compatibility with additional packages (sudo, nala, neofetch, net-tools, nmap)

This release ensures full compatibility with Debian 13 Trixie and Proxmox VE 9, providing users with the latest stable virtualization platform with enhanced security, performance, and feature set.

